The audition which opened on Nov. 29 would close Dec.13. The reality TV series was aimed to search for young talented individuals in Nigeria with singing competition. At the commencement of the audition, 30 eligible Nigerians are often selected for the show but only 12 contestants made it to final stage through voting.
The criteria for interested participants are “to record their 30 seconds video of them singing any song of their choice. “Upload it to www.Africa magic.tv/Nigerian Idol.
“Must be between 16 and 30 years old to participate.
